[1] New Caledonia
Date: Mon 7 Apr 2008
Source: Pacific Magazine, Oceania Flash report [edited]
<http://www.pacificmagazine.net/news/2008/04/07/leptospirosis-outbreak-in-new-caledonia>


With a dengue fever epidemic declared in February [2008] and still
uncontrolled, New Caledonia now has to combat water and
humidity-related diseases on another front, namely leptospirosis.

The dengue epidemic that has been affecting the capital Noumea and
its suburbs, but also the northeastern island if Lifou (Loyalty
island group) is now affecting over 320 persons, latest counts
revealed.

Prevention campaigns have intensified in the past few weeks and local
health services have urged the population to take heed of such simple
recommendations as cleaning any potential breeding site for the
_Aedes aegypti_ mosquito (the vector of the disease) larvae.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A map of Oceania showing the location of New Caledonia in the South
Pacific can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/australia/oceania_ref_2007.pdf>. - Mod.TY]

