[7] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Thu 10 Apr 2008
Source: O Tempo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://supernoticia.com.br/otempo/noticias/?IdNoticia=75939>


Yesterday [9 Apr 2008] the Municipal Health Secretariat confirmed the
1st case of dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) in Belo Horizonte this
year [2008]. The victim was a 17-year-old adolescent who lives in the
Pampulha region. He is now well and at home.

"We continue the [periodic anti-dengue sweeps] and campaigns," said
the Adjunct Municipal Secretary of Health, Maria do Carmo. In Minas
Gerais, 9385 cases of the disease have been registered this year
[2008], with 3 DHF cases and 2 deaths.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Globo cited a report of 9 Apr 2008 that for the same period in 2007
there was notification of 18 529 dengue cases in the entire state of
Minas Gerais
(<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Brasil/0,,MUL392392-5598,00-POLICIAIS+AJUDAM+NO+COMBATE+A+DENGUE+EM+MINAS+GERAIS.html>),
significantly more than for 2008 thus far.

A map of Brazil showing the location of Belo Horizonte in Minas
Gerais state can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>. - Mod.TY]

