[8] Brazil (Paraiba)
Date: Fri 11 Apr 2008
Source: Globo.com [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Brasil/0,,MUL396984-5598,00-DENGUE+HEMORRAGICA+MATA+CRIANCA+DE+ANOS+NA+PB+DIZ+GOVERNO.html>


A 4-year-old child died of DHF in Cuite. This was the 1st death
caused by dengue this year [2008] in the state [Paraiba]. According
to the Paraiba Health Secretariat, the total number of confirmed DHF
cases in the state, this year [2008], is 12.

Information provided by the Secretariat indicated that from January
[2008] up to this past Thursday [10 Apr 2008], 2882 [dengue] cases
were recorded in Paraiba. The most serious cases are among children
under age 10. The region with the greatest concentration of reported
cases in the state has been Sertao.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

