[9] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Fri 11 Apr 2008
Source: Globo.com [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Rio/0,,MUL398230-5606,00-RIO+REGISTRA+MAIS+DUAS+MORTES+POR+DENGUE.html>


The municipal Secretariat of Health confirmed 2 more dengue deaths in
Rio, increasing the number of deaths from dengue in the city to 50.
Currently, the number of [dengue] cases this year [2008] in the Rio
municipality has reached 48 643. There were 1631 new [dengue] cases
notified from Thursday to Friday [10-11 Apr 2008]

The official government total dengue deaths in the State of Rio as of
Wednesday (9 Apr 2008) reached 83 [for 2008].

The prefecture announced this Thursday (11 Apr 2008) that they will
increase the number of health posts this weekend [12-13 Apr 2008] to
reinforce patient care for those suspected of having dengue. On
Saturday (12 Apr 2008), the number will exceed 95, reaching 99 open
[health] posts. On Sunday (13 Apr 2008) 30 basic care units will be
functioning, instead of the 28 during the past week.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[ProMED-PORT cited a report in Agencia Brasil, in Portuguese, on 9
Apr 2008
(<http://www.agenciabrasil.gov.br:80/noticias/2008/04/09/materia.2008-04-09.9326881538/view>)
indicating that the State of Rio de Janeiro had registered more than
75 000 dengue cases this year (2008). Although the reports from other
areas in Brazil indicate a decline in the number of dengue cases, the
epidemic in Rio continues to be very serious. One hopes that the
additional patient care will keep the death rate low. - Mod.TY]

