[10] Brazil (Pernambuco)
Date: Thu 10 Apr 2008
Source: Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Brasil/0,,MUL395381-5598,00-DENGUE+MATA+MENINO+DE+ANOS+DIZ+PREFEITURA+DE+PERNAMBUCO.html>


Dengue killed an 8-year-old child according to the Pernambuco
prefecture. This is the 1st DHF death in the state this year [2008],
the government indicated. As of Wednesday [9 Apr 2008], the [Health]
Secretariat confirmed that there have been 317 cases of classical
dengue and 2 of DHF in the state [so far this year], compared to 495
classical dengue cases and 6 DHF cases during the same period last
year [2007].

